            </arrangement>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_6fed5ca805507597fecd45ddc809f2d4">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This series contains five photograph albums featuring gelatin silver prints of Geiringer's studio portraiture, personal photography, and travel photography. Many album pages contain manuscript captions in German.</p>
               <p>The first album contains eight studio portraits of young women, as well as one loose, undated digital print of a woman in a swimsuit, which appears to be from a different photo shoot and developed more recently.</p>
               <p>The second album contains Geiringer's personal portraits of family and friends, and travel photography from trips to the Swiss Alps and Rome, Italy. Sections of several album pages are cut out and missing, and some photographs have detached.</p>
               <p>The final three albums contain travel photographs from trips to Lower Austria and Yugoslavia in 1937. Locations in Lower Austria include Alland and Bad Deutsch-Altenburg. Locations in Yugoslavia include Dubrovnik, Lopud, Makarska, Sipan, and the Dalmatia region in present-day Croatia, as well as Kranjska Gora and Radlje ob Dravi in present-day Slovenia.</p>
               <p>This series also contains one postcard featuring a photograph of German actor Werner Krauss taken by Atelier Geiringer und Horovitz.</p>
            </scopecontent>
