            <scopecontent id="aspace_d04478b6b849159c98b20b77fea99850">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This series contains one scrapbook of clippings from German- and French-language publications featuring work by Atelier Geiringer und Horovitz. Subjects include fashion and studio portraits, and portraits of famous Austrians and Germans such as actors Elisabeth Bergner, Ernst Deustch, Tilla Durieux, and Oskar Karlweis, playwright Victor Barnowsky, poet Friedrich Gundolf, dramatist Georg Kaiser, and writers Jakob Wasserman and Thomas Mann. The scrapbook also includes pages from "Spemanns Literatur-Kalender," a 1929 calendar featuring Atelier Geiringer und Horovitz photographs.</p>
